12:21.040 --> 12:29.060
This is Daryl Lane and David Carson. Damon Knight's influence on science fiction
is indisputable, and it's made itself felt in many different ways. Knight was

12:29.060 --> 12:38.100
the originator of the Science Fiction Writers of America, for example, back in
1965. We asked him how the organization came about. About ten years earlier it

12:38.100 --> 12:47.380
must have been, and there was an effort to form a guild of science fiction
writers. And I went to one or two of their meetings, and it was pitiful because

12:47.380 --> 12:59.420
they used the parliamentary procedure, and they had 50 people all arguing. And
they finally hammered out a set of bylaws and elected officers, and then nothing

12:59.420 --> 13:08.060
happened. The officers all went home and just died. And I realized at that time
that there was a very easy way to do it. You didn't have to have the big

13:08.060 --> 13:16.620
meetings, and you didn't have to have all that apparatus. One person could do
it. But I didn't think I was conspicuous enough at that time. I didn't think

13:16.620 --> 13:34.400
anybody knew who I was. Later on, I was becoming more visible, and I realized
that I probably could do it. The precipitating event was by receiving in the

13:34.400 --> 13:47.780
same week three requests for anthology reprints for flat Cs, which I thought was
unfair to the author. So I wrote a flyer, the one-page thing, advising authors

13:47.780 --> 13:56.220
not to sign agreements for flat C anthology reprints, and saying, if you'd like
more information of this kind, send in your three bucks and become a charter

13:56.220 --> 14:06.640
member of SFWA. A flock of responses. And when I had about 78, I declared them
the charter members and wrote a set of bylaws and sent that around, and we were

14:06.640 --> 14:13.880
more or less in business. The Science Fiction Writers of America has helped
authors in various ways. For example, by helping them get better contracts from

14:13.880 --> 14:20.980
publishers, by fighting legal battles, and providing encouragement and
professional recognition. Another thing Knight was responsible for was to act as

14:20.980 --> 14:28.380
the co-founder of the Milford Science Fiction Writers Conference in 1956. The
Milford Conference was conceived by Knight and Judith Merrill as an aide to

14:28.380 --> 14:35.400
science fiction writers. It provided them with an opportunity to have their work
read and criticized by other professional science fiction writers. Knight talks

14:35.400 --> 14:45.040
about how the Milford Conference began. Well, this was in the mid-50s. And for
some reason, Judy Merrill and I got to talking about the idea of having a

14:45.040 --> 14:54.380
writer's conference in Milford, Pennsylvania, which is a very small town in the
Poconos. It was sort of the way you might talk about building a boat in your

14:54.380 --> 15:06.580
basement. And nothing was done about this until Judy and I went to the Worldcon
in Detroit, I think it was, and discovered that we were much more better than we

15:06.580 --> 15:17.100
realized. So that energized us, and we thought that possibly if we invited
people to Milford, they could actually come. And we sent out invitations. We got

15:17.100 --> 15:29.820
Jim Bush to join the masthead, lend it more respectability. And this was the
year in which the Worldcon, the following year, Worldcon was in New York. So it

15:29.820 --> 15:43.040
was easier for people to get out there directly afterwards. And we got 40
people. Just amazing. It was quite intense. We had evening discussions that went

15:43.040 --> 15:50.280
on for several hours. People raising the forest of hands to do the next to
speak. Quite exciting.

16:01.460 --> 16:08.020
A regular feature of the conference was the workshop, in which authors would
submit manuscripts and have them criticized by other members of the conference.

16:08.280 --> 16:15.720
Damon Knight and his wife, Kate Wilhelm, now conduct the Clarion Workshop in
science fiction and fantasy. The Clarion Workshop is based on the same idea as

16:15.720 --> 16:22.500
the Milford Workshop, though attending writers are beginners for the most part,
and Knight and Wilhelm are the teachers. Professional writers of science fiction

16:22.500 --> 16:28.860
and beginning writers, too, who have hopes of becoming established
professionals, have a great deal to thank Damon Knight for. We'll talk with

16:28.860 --> 16:30.760
Damon Knight about one of his novels on our next show.

